SUPLINF.P:
The Regulatory Flexibility Act (RFA) (5 U.S.C. 601 
et seq.
) generally requires an agency to conduct a regulatory flexibility analysis of any rule subject to notice and comment rulemaking requirements, unless the agency certifies that the rule will not have a significant economic impact on a substantial number of small entities. This Final Rule updates HUD's uniform standards for determining when a housing practice with a discriminatory effect violates the Fair Housing Act. Given the recent Supreme Court decision, HUD's objective in this rule is to ensure consistency and uniformity, and therefore reduce burden for all who may be involved in a challenged practice.
